# Python
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# Per-machine runtime state (window position/size, plan, pinned reset, the last
# numbers you synced from Settings -> Usage). Pitwall recreates this from DEFAULTS in
# ts_core.py on first run — it is intentionally NOT shared. (The token_steward_*
# names are the pre-Pitwall files, still ignored so an unmigrated dev box stays clean.)
pitwall_config.json
token_steward_config.json

# Per-machine drift log — what the widget guessed vs what you synced from
# Settings -> Usage. Personal usage data, recreated locally; NOT shared.
pitwall_corrections.jsonl
token_steward_corrections.jsonl

# Internal working notes (overnight reviews, standups) — not for the public repo.
docs/standup/

# Internal docs moved to the private pitwall-internal repo (K6, 2026-06-13): the
# Claude↔Codex coordination log, the security review log, and the bake-off salvage.
# Ignored here so they can't be re-tracked into the public tree.
TEAM_NOTES.md
docs/plans/security-review-log.md
docs/apple-redesign-salvage/
# Moved to pitwall-internal 2026-06-14 (pre-public team review): the internal design
# log, the CLI-alignment engineering note, and the dated security reviews — all
# internal-facing, not user docs.
DESIGN_NOTES.md
docs/token-metrics-and-cli-alignment.md
docs/security/

# "Let it ride" / autonomous-mode design, security & marketing — NOT for the public
# repo (lives in the private pitwall-internal repo). Belt-and-suspenders: also covered
# once moved under pitwall-internal/.
pitwall-internal/
docs/let-it-ride-*
docs/security/let-it-ride-*
docs/marketing/
docs/plans/let-it-ride-*
docs/plans/real-usage-auto-sync-investigation.md

# POC / spike / dev-verification scratch — not product code
poc/

# Build/packaging pipeline — kept LOCAL only (decision 2026-06-14). Pitwall ships
# free + source-only (no .exe), and the release checklist carries internal process
# detail (decision codes, model-routing tags, owner name), so the whole build/ tree
# stays out of the public repo.
build/

# Bug-repro screen recordings + extracted frames / debug screenshots (not product).
# Underscore-prefixed docs paths are throwaway captures by convention.
*.mp4
docs/_*
docs/paint-test/

# Internal orientation files for the AI team (name the codename + local paths) —
# they live on disk for sessions but never ship to the public repo.
CLAUDE.md
AGENTS.md

# Worker-dispatch artifacts (model-routing system) — internal task/report traffic.
worker_tasks_*.md
worker_report_*.md

# Local dev scratch: GUI-driver helpers, verification screenshots, spike pocs.
# All throwaway — not product code.
tools/
*.log

